name: Florida Panthers
summary: The Edmonton Oilers and Florida Panthers are facing off in the Stanley Cup Final, a matchup of two teams with contrasting backgrounds. The Panthers, a first-time finalist, are riding a wave of momentum after sweeping the Presidents Trophy-winning Colorado Avalanche in the second round and then defeating the heavily favored Tampa Bay Lightning in the Eastern Conference Final. The Oilers, meanwhile, are making their sixth appearance in the Final, but their first since 2006. Game 1 of the series resulted in a 3-0 shutout victory for the Panthers, with goalie Sergei Bobrovsky making 32 saves. The series continues with Game 2 in Edmonton on Saturday night.

name: Rebecca Grossman
summary: Rebecca Grossman, a socialite and co-founder of the Burn Foundation, has been sentenced to 15 years to life in prison for the deaths of two young boys in a 2020 hit-and-run incident in Los Angeles. Grossman was under the influence of alcohol and prescription drugs at the time of the crash, which occurred in a crosswalk. The prosecutors had sought a sentence of 34 years to life, while Grossman's attorneys argued for a shorter term of 6 years. The judge ultimately imposed a sentence that falls between the two requests. The case has drawn significant attention due to Grossman's connections and the tragic loss of life.

summary: Nvidia's recent stock split, which divided each share into 10 smaller ones, caused a surge in its stock price. The move aimed to make Nvidia's shares more accessible to smaller investors. name: Tony Evans
summary: Prominent pastor and author Dr. Tony Evans has announced his resignation from his leadership role at Oak Cliff Bible Fellowship in Dallas, Texas. Citing an undisclosed "sin," Evans has decided to step down from his pastoral duties to focus on "spiritual recovery and healing." The news has shocked and saddened the congregation, as Evans has been a beloved figure in the community for decades. The exact nature of the sin has not been revealed, but it is believed to have occurred in the past and is not related to any current allegations or improprieties. Evans has expressed his deep regret and stated that he is committed to accountability and repentance. The church is currently in the process of appointing an interim pastor and supporting Evans during this challenging time.
